                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d545">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Pierrepont</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-07-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 19, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s July 18. At the request of the Chilean minister for foreign affairs
                    1 to-day handed to him a copy of the protocol. The Argentine and Brazilian
                    ministers not yet having instructions, I ventured the private opinion that he
                    could exercise a very salutary influence on Ecuador. This brought forth the
                    renewed assurance of cooperation and of desire to promote peace.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Pierrepont.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
